THIS IS ME. The real me. January 2023 🌟 Holiday lbs, no makeup, pimples… HUMAN. Going into this New Year I want to be more raw with y’all. The 1st week of 2023 has gone by already - I can’t believe how fast time is going. I challenged myself in so many ways this week including becoming a new instructor for the @lagreefitness method; a goal I really wanted to achieve a few months back and thought I never would ((KEEP BELIEVING IN YOURSELF)). 

In the past, I would never post iPhone pictures on here. I made sure anything I put on the internet was flawless and taken by a “professional.” But that’s not who I am anymore. Becoming a group fitness instructor, health advocate, & soon to be personal trainer/coach… I value the message I put out to the public more than ever. I am human. The holidays got to me. I ate whatever I wanted and didn’t train as much as I wanted too at the gym. But that’s OKAY. What matters is how we pick ourselves up when we want to make that CHANGE. 

This month I am diving back to pushing myself to that next level - recreating consistency & discipline for who I am right now in this moment. Drinking more Kangen water, starting my day off with a green juice, taking my superfoods supplements/vitamins, eating cleaner, reading, journaling, meditating, adventuring… & so much more that I want to get back into. 

I’m not really sure what the point of this post is. Maybe a “hey, I’m feeling the stress of wanting to get my shit together but feel like it’s so hard to start & get there.” I hear you. I look back to photos of me in the summer & I’m like danggggggg I miss her. But it’s time to evolve once more & fall in love with someone new that’s dying to come out of me 💗 Life is about continuous growth. 

Happy Friday! Always here for you. Xoxo💋 #fitnessmotivation

social_posts.post_text: Success OR failure with your fitness goals can snowball. You can add up small wins that turn into big wins OR you can have a minor setback which cumulates major setbacks, & could lead to giving up your goals altogether. REMEMBER: You aren't a robot where a set of actions will produce a predictable output. Instead, you can influence your body through diet and exercise, but HOW it changes isn't entirely predictable or under your control. This is why it's helpful to FOCUS ON THE PROCESS and what you can control to keep moving forward when you think change isn't happening (or happening fast enough). Something I’ve been working on all month in this New Year… Also can you believe we are already halfway through January!!! YOU GOT THIS 💪🏼 We are in this together 💙 #processoveroutcome #mindsetmatters #nevergiveup

The best versions of ourselves don't come out when everything is going amazing - The best versions of ourselves come out in the midst of trial…. Because that's where we grow 🦋 That's where our real substance comes out. That's where you find the person you were always meant to be 🤍 The person who was there all along. 

P.S. I love this swimsuit from @oneoneswim - it fits so well on my body & I feel really comfortable swimming in it!

Happy Hump Day Fam 💙 A little message from me to you… All you’ll ever need is a little discipline to get started. But when you feel like quitting, you must remember your why. When you keep showing up day after day, your fitness journey will begin to feel like it’s part of your everyday routine. Like mine, your fitness lifestyle will begin to evolve and change over time. I’ve done it all… from CrossFit, to Pilates, Spin, Personal Training. I rarely have a “perfect” day in any of of those environments, but I also won’t let that deter me from feeling better from the inside out! How we move our bodies daily impacts our mental health, physical health, & overall well-being. So get comfortable with the fact that change takes time! TRUST ME. Just show up, and give it what you can. Promise yourself you will never regret sticking to it and seeing yourself reach what you never thought was possible. YOU GOT THIS 💪🏼 p.s. the ending of the video is the best part 😆 #humpday #discipline #workout

BUILD & BELIEVE ⭐️

I’m excited to announce my NEW group fitness class at @mauipowerhousegym @studiocyclemaui 🥳 Join me for Build & Believe every Tuesday & Thursday at 5PM 🎉 This is a 50-minute weight training class that targets different muscle groups each session, using effective exercises to promote strength and leanness. Gain knowledge of proper form, muscle engagement, and gym-floor movements, eliminating the fear of learning unfamiliar exercises by yourself. No need to weight train alone when you can train with Nickole 😉 Classes will target biceps, back, core, triceps, glutes, shoulders, quads, hamstrings & so much more! 1st class is on Tuesday, July 11th. Give us a try for only $5 per class, or take advantage of our special offer: 8 classes for just $35 ✅ Reserve your spot today on our app! #mauipowerhousegym #strengthtraining #liftwithaloha

Life is about risks, right? Bet on YOURSELF. Challenge YOURSELF 🦋 Weekly check-in ✅ This morning I weight 143.4 with 19.4% body fat! I lost 3 pounds in a week 🤯 A LOT more work left to do, however WE OFF TO A GOOD START 🥳 

I know that sharing my journey will help keep me motivated and accountable to the process. I'm human and thoughts of self-doubt enter my mind, especially when starting something so NEW/NEVER done before. I had many highs this week as well as some lows - what kept me going was my WHY… Competing for me is not about being better than anyone. It's about believing in MYSELF, that I can do hard things, & be braver than I believed I was. 

A few things I learned this week… 1) PREP IS HARD - basically a 2nd job (you’re always thinking about it 😅) 2) SUPPORT IS IMPORTANT - having a tight circle of people that love you is crucial (they make your life easier not harder) 3) YOUR JOURNEY IS NOT A RACE TO THE FINISH LINE - stop counting down the days & focus on the now (enjoy the process)! 

Enjoy my few highlights of this week 😉 ALSO a quick shoutout to MY BABE @darrenkfryer for being on the front window at the Wailea Shops outside of our favorite store @kaialohasupply ✨ Manifesting never does us wrong ❤️ Extremely grateful for everything happening in our lives!

I wish I knew this earlier in my fitness journey... 💪🏼 Muscle gain is about challenging your body (lifting HEAVY) AND eating to fuel growth 🔥 Fat loss is about calorie deficit, exercise has little to do with it 🍗 Nutrition is key – calories + macronutrients must be aligned with YOUR body, goal, and food needs/preferences! 8 POUNDS DOWN IN JUST 36 DAYS 🥳 I’m so astonished by this process and really thankful I decided to go down this route. One day… it just didn’t feel right anymore. The façade I was presenting to the world, wasn’t the real me. I built my “character” for so long that it became my life 24/7. This party girl, reality tv personality, TikTok influencer, and model wasn’t serving me/my greater purpose. It’s been almost 3 years since I stepped away from the life I made for almost 8 years. I was SO scared. I knew nothing else but what I was doing, which was nothing that made me truly happy. Being officially 8 days away from my 1st bodybuilding show has me in all the feels because I really feel like I’m evolving into who I’ve always wanted to be… in control of my own life. Let me be your sign, that if you want change… GO DO IT. It won’t happen over night, and it won’t be all peaches & cream - you will feel lonely. However, all these little obstacles teach you something to carry you through the rest of life. To protect you from going down the same rabbit hole again, and again, and again. Change comes within you, make that 1st step today 🫶

As you prepare for all possible outcomes, may you also remember to prepare for positive outcomes, too. May you prepare yourself for good memories, good lessons, and all of the little places where sunlight will come shining through ☀️ Happy Monday friends!

Friendly reminder that the best life is a balanced life 🫶

It’s good to eat healthy, lift heavy, & get movement in /// It’s also 💯 ok to eat food just because it brings you joy! Making progress & being healthy is basically like balancing your bank account. As long as the sum of your choices makes a positive average (over weeks, months, & years), the indulgences won’t completely undo all your hard work 🙏 Your health & fitness lifestyle should be enjoyable 🤍 This is what creates sustainability, & sustainability for life is the magic pill for achieving results and keeping them!
